d the hundreds of varieties he grew, the half-Virginian half-French cuisine he developed, and the gardening traditions he adapted from many other countries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aJefferson, Thomas, -- 1743-1826 -- Homes and haunts -- Virginia. 0aMonticello (Va.). 0aVegetable gardening -- Virginia. 0aVegetable gardeningzVirginia. 7aNATURE / Plants / General.2bisacsh1 aBowman, Leslie Greene, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWaters, Alice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWaters, Alice.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030018340540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300183405423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300183405/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles